title: IND vs ENG: 'Do you think the jawans complain about the cold?' - Gavaskar

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: The Anderson-Tendulkar Trophy witnessed heated exchanges between India and England players. Despite the tension, Ben Stokes downplayed the incidents. India secured a thrilling six-run victory in the fifth Test. This resulted in a 2-2 draw in the series. Mohammed Siraj's outstanding bowling performance led India to victory. He took five wickets in the final innings.
title: IND vs ENG Test | Ben Stokes on verbal duels: 'Pretty sure no one's crying''

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Mohammed Siraj's stellar performance in the fifth Test against England led to widespread admiration. The Telangana Police congratulated the Hyderabad-born pacer. Fans humorously demanded Siraj's promotion within the police force. Siraj is currently a Deputy Superintendent of Police under the sports quota. He ended the series as the highest wicket-taker. His performance helped India level the series.
title: India fans make unusual demands after Telangana Police congratulates DSP Siraj

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Stock market recommendations: Mirae Asset Sharekhan suggests selling Naukri and Tata Motors. Naukri, trading below its 200 DMA, is expected to decline to Rs 1320, while Tata Motors, having broken a consolidation pattern, is projected to fall to Rs 585.
title: Top stocks to sell today: Recommendations for August 5- check list

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Gautam Gambhir's passionate celebrations highlighted India's dramatic six-run victory over England at The Oval, securing a 2-2 series draw. The win, fueled by Mohammed Siraj's five-wicket haul, marked a turning point for Gambhir's coaching tenure after facing initial challenges. Under Shubman Gill's captaincy, the team displayed resilience and fighting spirit throughout the intense Test series.
title: Watch: Gambhir and India coaches go wild after win at The Oval

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Sunil Gavaskar's 'lucky jacket,' worn during India's Gabba Test victory in 2021, resurfaced during the thrilling India vs England series finale. Gavaskar proudly displayed the jacket after India's dramatic six-run victory at The Oval, which levelled the series 2-2. He had hinted at wearing it, believing it would bring luck, and indeed, India secured a memorable win.
title: IND vs ENG: Gavaskar flaunts his 'lucky jacket' after India level series 2-2 - Watch

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: At Buffalo Bills training camp, Josh Allen impressed with his on-field performance, connecting with receivers despite injuries. The highlight, however, was a heartwarming reunion with Annabella and Blake, two Champion kids from Oishei Children’s Hospital. Allen, who supports the hospital through the Patricia Allen Fund, shared selfies and signed autographs, creating a memorable moment beyond the game.
title: Josh Allen delights at Bills camp: Reunites with Oishei Children’s Hospital; touching fan moment

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: India defeated England in a thrilling Test match at The Oval, with the series ending in a 2-2 draw. Mohammed Siraj took five wickets. Suniel Shetty's enthusiastic celebration went viral. Ahan Shetty and Athiya Shetty shared their excitement online. Other Bollywood stars like Kareena Kapoor Khan and Anil Kapoor also celebrated the victory. The win sparked national pride and celebration.
title: Viral video: Wild! KL Rahul's father-in-law Suniel Shetty goes crazy after India win

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Mohit Suri's romantic drama 'Saiyaara' starring Ahaan Panday and Aneet Padda made over Rs 300 crore. The film slowed down in its third week. 'Saiyaara' earned Rs 172.75 crore in its first week and Rs 107.75 crore in the second. New releases like 'Mahavtar Narsimha', 'Son Of Sardaar 2', and 'Dhadak 2' are now in cinemas.
title: ‘Saiyaara’ Box Office: Film past Rs 302 cr mark in India; lowest single-day earning on third Monday

author: TNN
description: A government girls' school in Madhya Pradesh is grappling with a cobra infestation, as 25 baby cobras have been found in the last two weeks. The alarming situation has forced the school to close classrooms, disrupting lessons for over 1000 students. Authorities are working to seal potential snake nests and ensure the safety of everyone.
title: 25 baby cobras in 15 days: MP school shuts classrooms; digs floors to end snake scare

author: TNN
description: Surat police raided a hotel party at 'Weekend Address' following a tip about liquor consumption, arresting six individuals, including two female artists and four businessmen. The raid, triggered by a family dispute where a man reported his daughter-in-law's presence, led to the seizure of liquor and glasses.
title: Father-in-law tips off cops about booze party in Surat hotel; all arrested
